Sentencas: The cobalt-free perovskite oxide, Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-delta (BSFN), was investigated as a new cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (ITSOFCs).
Titulo: Cobalt-free perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrical conductivity of BSFN reaches the maximum value of 14.1 S cm(-1) at 450 degrees C.
Titulo: Cobalt-free perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The average thermal expansion coefficient of BSFN is about 19.2 x 10(-6)
Titulo: Cobalt-free perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: K-1 from room temperature to 1000 degrees C.
Titulo: Cobalt-free perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The area specific resistance of the BSFN cathode is as low as 0.082 Omega cm(2) at 700 degrees C. A maximum power density of 745 mW cm(-2) is obtained at 700 degrees C for the single cell with the BSFN cathode.
Titulo: Cobalt-free perovskite Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ as a cathode material for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Our results suggest that the cobalt-free oxide BSFN is a very promising cathode material for application in ITSOFCs.
